name: aubergine production, open field | aubergine | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/19482/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of fresh aubergine in an irrigated open field. The crop cycle lasts circa 3.5 months and yields 26250 kg of aubergines. Mineral NPK fertilizer input is 104-48-24 kg/ha. Organic fertilizer applied amounts to 60,000 kg of manure from cattle dung. Pesticides used has active ingredient of Carbofuran 450g/ha and Chlorantranilipore 10g/ha. In case of Chlorantranilipore, the ingredient Clothianidin is used as proxy for this dataset. Machinery is used only for soil cultivation with fuel consumption of 12.48 kg/ha using plough and rotary cultivator for soil tillage. ;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:]

This activity starts about four and half weeks after the harvest of the previous crop. The soil is prepared for cultivation in mid-January and sowing of seeds started about three weeks after soil preparation. 

The activity ends with the harvesting of the mature aubergine from the aubergine field.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/011:Growing of non-perennial crops/0113:Growing of vegetables and melons, roots and tubers

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Soil cultivating date for the main crop: 17-January, 2016; Harvesting date main crop: 15-May, 2016. The soil cultivation, sowing and harvesting dates are taken as the middle date of the week or fortnight told to the data collector by the farmer. Total time from date of sowing to date of harvesting comes to 100 days.  The data is collected for one crop cycle. The cycle of one year is considered for entry in ecoeditor.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Cultivation of Brinjal follows conventional production standards
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The dataset has been extrapolated from the respective Indian dataset. Uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The farmer was identified and contacted by agriculture science faculty familiar with the local farmers in the region. Data was collected directly from the farmer through semi-structured interview using a questionnaire based on the input requirements Ecoinvent LCI calculation tool for crop production.
